# 🏛️ Repository Pattern

**This is a CURSOR-SPECIFIC rule file.**

**Full documentation:** [docs/standards/rules/repository-pattern.md](../../docs/standards/rules/repository-pattern.md)

## Rule for Cursor

Cursor MUST enforce repository pattern:

- **NEVER** suggest direct Supabase calls in apps
- **ALWAYS** use repositories from `@workspace/supabase-data`
- **FAIL** if direct DB access detected

## Quick Reference

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT - Use repository
import { TaskRepository } from "@workspace/supabase-data/modules/tasks"

const repo = new TaskRepository(supabase)
const task = await repo.findById(id)

// ❌ FORBIDDEN - Direct Supabase
const { data } = await supabase.from("tasks").select().eq("id", id)
```

## Structure

```
packages/supabase-data/src/modules/{module}/
├── domain/
│   ├── dto/
│   ├── schemas/
│   └── ports/
└── infrastructure/
    ├── mappers/
    └── repositories/
```

